in the very seats we left them in.

1616
02:06:21,681 --> 02:06:25,310
Double-zero 23 and double-zero
24, if my memory serves.

1617
02:06:26,060 --> 02:06:29,480
Explosives still around their
ankles, still ready to explode.

1618
02:06:29,564 --> 02:06:32,817
And your mission, some
would call a terrorist plot,

1619
02:06:32,900 --> 02:06:35,403
as of this moment,
is still a go.

1620
02:06:35,486 --> 02:06:38,823
That's a pretty exciting story.
What's next? Eliza on Ice?

1621
02:06:38,906 --> 02:06:40,158
However,

1622
02:06:42,035 --> 02:06:45,163
all I have to do is pick up
this phone right here,

1623
02:06:45,246 --> 02:06:48,082
inform the cinema,
and your plan is kaput.

1624
02:06:50,501 --> 02:06:55,715
If they're still here, and if they're
still alive, and that's one big if,

1625
02:06:57,050 --> 02:06:58,843
there ain't no way you're
going to take them boys

1626
02:06:58,927 --> 02:07:00,553
without setting off
them bombs.

1627
02:07:00,637 --> 02:07:02,388
I have no doubt.

1628
02:07:02,472 --> 02:07:05,767
And, yes, some Germans will die.
Yes, it will ruin the evening.

1629
02:07:05,850 --> 02:07:08,770
And, yes, Goebbels will be
very, very, very mad at you

1630
02:07:08,853 --> 02:07:10,939
for what you've done
to his big night.

1631
02:07:12,190 --> 02:07:14,484
But you won't get Hitler,
you won't get Goebbels,

1632
02:07:14,567 --> 02:07:17,612
you won't get Goring,
and you won't get Bormann.

1633
02:07:17,695 --> 02:07:20,281
And you need all four
to end the war.

1634
02:07:21,950 --> 02:07:25,119
But if I don't pick up
this phone right here,

1635
02:07:25,203 --> 02:07:27,538
you may very well
get all four.

1636
02:07:28,790 --> 02:07:33,628
And if you get all four,
you end the war

1637
02:07:34,879 --> 02:07:36,130
tonight.

1638
02:07:37,507 --> 02:07:39,050
So, gentlemen,

1639
02:07:39,759 --> 02:07:42,971
let's discuss the prospect
of ending the war tonight.

1640
02:07:45,890 --> 02:07:47,725
So, the way I see it,

1641
02:07:47,809 --> 02:07:52,021
since Hitler's death or possible
rescue rests solely on my reaction,

1642
02:07:52,689 --> 02:07:54,274
if I do nothing,

1643
02:07:54,691 --> 02:07:57,402
it's as if I'm causing his
death even more than yourselves.

1644
02:07:57,485 --> 02:07:58,736
Wouldn't you agree?

1645
02:07:59,404 --> 02:08:00,738
I guess so.

1646
02:08:03,324 --> 02:08:05,326
How about you,
Utivich?

1647
02:08:05,410 --> 02:08:07,036
I guess so, too.

1648
02:08:12,583 --> 02:08:13,835
Gentlemen,
I have no intention

1649
02:08:13,918 --> 02:08:17,005
of killing Hitler and killing Goebbels and
killing Goring and killing Bormann,

1650
02:08:17,088 --> 02:08:19,841
not to mention winning the war
single-handedly for the Allies,

1651
02:08:19,924 --> 02:08:23,678
only later to find myself standing
before a Jewish tribunal.

1652
02:08:25,763 --> 02:08:29,309
If you want to win
the war tonight,

1653
02:08:30,935 --> 02:08:33,104
we have to make a deal.

1654
02:08:36,107 --> 02:08:37,859
What kind of deal?

1655
02:08:37,942 --> 02:08:40,486
The kind you wouldn't
have the authority to make.

1656
02:08:40,570 --> 02:08:45,116
However, I'm sure this mission of yours has
a commanding officer.

1657
02:08:46,117 --> 02:08:47,452
A general.

1658
02:08:48,119 --> 02:08:49,787
I'm betting for...

1659
02:08:51,497 --> 02:08:53,416
OSS would be my guess.

1660
02:08:57,337 --> 02:08:59,797
That's a bingo!

1661
02:09:02,800 --> 02:09:05,303
Is that the way you say it?
"That's a bingo. "

1662
02:09:05,386 --> 02:09:07,263
You just say, "Bingo. "

1663
02:09:07,347 --> 02:09:09,599
Bingo! How fun.

1664
02:09:12,018 --> 02:09:15,104
But I digress. Where were we?
Yeah! Make a deal.

1665
02:09:15,647 --> 02:09:20,068
Over there is a very capable
two-way radio and sitting behind it

1666
02:09:20,151 --> 02:09:24,322
is a more than capable
radio operator named Hermann.

1667
02:09:24,656 --> 02:09:26,991
Get me someone on the other end
of that radio

1668
02:09:27,075 --> 02:09:30,119
with the power of the pen
to authorize my,

1669
02:09:30,203 --> 02:09:33,122
let's call it, the terms of my
conditional surrender.

1670
02:09:33,206 --> 02:09:35,625
If that tastes better
going down.

1671
02:09:36,417 --> 02:09:37,669
You know,
where I'm from...

1672
02:09:37,752 --> 02:09:39,629
Yeah?
Where is that exactly?

1673
02:09:39,712 --> 02:09:41,756
Maynardville,
Tennessee.

1674
02:09:41,839 --> 02:09:44,300
I've done my share
of bootlegging.

1675
02:09:44,509 --> 02:09:48,179
U p there, if you engage in what the federal
government calls illegal activity,

1676
02:09:48,263 --> 02:09:50,390
but what we call just a man trying to
make a living for his family

1677
02:09:50,473 --> 02:09:54,894
selling moonshine liquor, it behooves
oneself to keep his wits.

1678
02:09:56,854 --> 02:10:00,275
Long story short, we hear a story
too good to be true,

1679
02:10:00,942 --> 02:10:02,193
it ain't.

1680
02:10:04,028 --> 02:10:06,781
Sitting in your chair, I would probably
say the same thing,

1681
02:10:06,864 --> 02:10:11,577
and 999,999 times out of a million,
you would be correct.

1682
02:10:13,579 --> 02:10:17,166
But in the pages of history,
every once in a while,

1683
02:10:17,750 --> 02:10:21,129
fate reaches out
and extends its hand.

1684
02:10:27,969 --> 02:10:29,929
What shall
the history books read?

1685
02:10:56,789 --> 02:11:00,001
I implore you.
We must destroy that tower.

1686
02:11:01,419 --> 02:11:03,046
Sarge, that tower...

1687
02:11:22,607 --> 02:11:24,525
The tower stands!

1688
02:11:26,769 --> 02:11:27,811
Gum?

1689
02:11:31,658 --> 02:11:34,160
Psst! Psst!

1690
02:12:14,984 --> 02:12:16,068
It's time.

1691
02:12:17,862 --> 02:12:20,655
I should go lock the auditorium and
take my place behind the screen.

1692
02:14:04,269 --> 02:14:06,437
So when the military history
of this night is written,

1693
02:14:06,521 --> 02:14:10,191
it will be recorded that I was part
of Operation Kino

1694
02:14:10,275 --> 02:14:13,069
from the very beginning
as a double agent.

1695
02:14:13,152 --> 02:14:17,198
Anything I've done in my guise
as an SS Colonel

1696
02:14:17,282 --> 02:14:20,326
was sanctioned by the OSS
as a necessary evil

1697
02:14:20,410 --> 02:14:23,121
to establish my cover
with the Germans.

1698
02:14:23,329 --> 02:14:26,624
And it was my placement of
Lieutenant Raine's dynamite

1699
02:14:26,708 --> 02:14:29,669
in Hitler and Goebbels'
opera box that assured their demise.

1700
02:14:30,703 --> 02:14:33,371
I informed the Führer that the
audience has taken their seats.

1701
02:14:33,456 --> 02:14:34,831
He should arrive any minute.

1702
02:14:36,292 --> 02:14:37,292
Thank you, Hans.

1703
02:14:46,811 --> 02:14:49,814
By the way, that last part
is actually true.

1704
02:14:49,897 --> 02:14:54,819
I want my full military pension and benefits
under my proper rank.

1705
02:14:55,153 --> 02:14:57,572
I want to receive the Congressional
Medal of Honor

1706
02:14:57,655 --> 02:15:01,618
for my invaluable assistance in the toppling
of the Third Reich.

1707
02:15:03,036 --> 02:15:06,122
In fact, I want all the members of
Operation Kino

1708
02:15:06,205 --> 02:15:09,167
to receive the
Congressional Medal of Honor.

1709
02:15:09,542 --> 02:15:13,254
Full citizenship for myself.
Well, that goes without saying.

1710
02:15:13,546 --> 02:15:16,758
And I would like
the United States of America

1711
02:15:16,841 --> 02:15:20,929
to purchase property for me
on Nantucket Island

1712
02:15:21,012 --> 02:15:24,265
as a reward for all the countless lives
I've saved

1713
02:15:24,349 --> 02:15:26,684
by bringing the tyranny
of the National Socialist Party

1714
02:15:26,768 --> 02:15:30,396
to a swifter-than-imagined end.
Do you have all that, sir?

1715
02:15:32,190 --> 02:15:35,652
I look forward to seeing you
face to face as well, sir.

1716
02:15:36,527 --> 02:15:38,738
Lieutenant Raine?
Right here.

1717
02:15:41,950 --> 02:15:43,159
Yes, sir.

1718
02:15:43,242 --> 02:15:46,996
Colonel Landa will put you and Private
Utivich in a truck as prisoners.

1719
02:15:47,080 --> 02:15:51,459
Then he and his radio operator will
get in the truck and drive to our lines.

1720
02:15:51,542 --> 02:15:56,130
Upon crossing our lines, Colonel Landa
and his man will surrender to you.

1721
02:15:56,214 --> 02:15:58,758
You will then take over
driving of the truck

1722
02:15:58,841 --> 02:16:02,220
and bring them straight to me for
debriefing. Is that clear, Lieutenant?

1723
02:16:02,303 --> 02:16:03,429
Yes, sir.

1724
02:16:03,513 --> 02:16:04,973
Over and out.

1725
02:16:29,488 --> 02:16:32,824
