I want my money back.

1731
02:17:56,826 --> 02:17:58,326
That actor in the movie stinks.

1732
02:18:00,663 --> 02:18:01,746
What are you doing here?

1733
02:18:01,997 --> 02:18:03,039
I came to visit you.

1734
02:18:04,375 --> 02:18:05,417
Can't you see how busy I am?

1735
02:18:05,709 --> 02:18:07,210
Then allow me to lend an assist.

1736
02:18:08,504 --> 02:18:10,338
Fredrick, it's not funny, you can't be here.

1737
02:18:11,340 --> 02:18:13,591
This is your premiere,
you need to be out there with them.

1738
02:18:16,720 --> 02:18:17,846
Normally, you would be right.

1739
02:18:19,014 --> 02:18:20,348
And for all the other films I do...

1740
02:18:21,016 --> 02:18:23,852
...I intend to endure evenings like tonight,
in the proper spirit.

1741
02:18:26,021 --> 02:18:27,230
However, the fact remains...

1742
02:18:28,357 --> 02:18:30,442
...this film is based
on my military exploits.

1743
02:18:31,068 --> 02:18:34,696
And in this case,
my exploits consisted of killing many men.

1744
02:18:36,198 --> 02:18:38,199
Consequently, the part of
the film that's playing now...

1745
02:18:40,619 --> 02:18:42,036
...I don't like watching this part.

1746
02:18:43,873 --> 02:18:45,707
I am sorry, Fredrick, but...
- So, I thought...

1747
02:18:46,041 --> 02:18:48,251
...l'd come up here
and do what I do best...

1748
02:18:48,586 --> 02:18:49,711
...annoy you.

1749
02:18:50,713 --> 02:18:53,715
And from the look on your face,
it would appear I haven't lost my touch.

1750
02:18:55,384 --> 02:18:57,343
Are you so used to
the Nazis kissing your ass...

1751
02:18:57,428 --> 02:18:58,928
...you've forgotten what
the word "no" means?

1752
02:18:59,555 --> 02:19:01,473
No... you can't be here!

1753
02:19:01,640 --> 02:19:02,724
Now go away!

1754
02:19:05,644 --> 02:19:06,728
Fredrick, you hurt me.

1755
02:19:07,062 --> 02:19:11,399
Well, it's nice to know you can feel something.

1756
02:19:12,234 --> 02:19:14,068
Even if it's just physical pain.

1757
02:19:14,737 --> 02:19:16,613
I'm not a man you say, "go away" to.

1758
02:19:17,656 --> 02:19:21,826
There's over three hundred dead bodies in Italy,
that if they could, would testify to that!

1759
02:19:24,455 --> 02:19:25,622
After what I've done for you...

1760
02:19:25,998 --> 02:19:28,082
...you disrespect me at your peril!

1761
02:19:28,417 --> 02:19:29,501
Lock the door.

1762
02:19:30,044 --> 02:19:31,085
What?

1763
02:19:32,379 --> 02:19:33,421
Lock the door.

1764
02:19:33,506 --> 02:19:34,589
We don't have much time.

1765
02:19:37,760 --> 02:19:38,843
Time for what?

1766
02:19:39,762 --> 02:19:40,845
Forget it!

1767
02:19:41,096 --> 02:19:42,263
No, no, no... wait.

1768
02:19:43,933 --> 02:19:45,892
You want me to... lock the door?

1769
02:19:46,602 --> 02:19:47,769
For the fifty-seventh time, yes.

1770
02:21:49,150 --> 02:21:51,736
When I kill that guy,
you got 30 feet to get to that guard.

1771
02:21:51,819 --> 02:21:53,780
Can you do it?
I have to.

1772
02:22:24,018 --> 02:22:25,353
Champagne?

1773
02:22:47,116 --> 02:22:49,117
Extraordinary my dear,
simply extraordinary!

1774
02:22:49,618 --> 02:22:50,952
This is your finest film yet.

1775
02:22:52,955 --> 02:22:54,288
Thank you, my Führer.

1776
02:22:56,458 --> 02:22:57,500
Thank you.

1777
02:23:17,196 --> 02:23:19,907
Who wants to send
a message to Germany?

1778
02:23:20,742 --> 02:23:23,077
I have a message
for Germany.

1779
02:23:26,539 --> 02:23:28,791
That you are
all going to die.

1780
02:23:29,867 --> 02:23:31,200
Enough! Stop it!

1781
02:23:31,326 --> 02:23:32,368
Turn off the projector!

1782
02:23:32,545 --> 02:23:37,967
And I want you to look deep into the face of
the Jew who's going to do it!

1783
02:23:38,167 --> 02:23:40,042
I don't know what's going on.
That does not belong in my movie!

1784
02:23:40,053 --> 02:23:43,139
Marcel, burn it down.

1785
02:23:44,140 --> 02:23:45,642
Oui, Shosanna.

1786
02:24:21,094 --> 02:24:23,221
My name
is Shosanna Dreyfus,

1787
02:24:23,596 --> 02:24:25,181
and this is the face

1788
02:24:27,141 --> 02:24:29,477
of Jewish vengeance.

1789
02:26:25,542 --> 02:26:28,002
These are the American lines, Colonel sir.

1790
02:26:35,144 --> 02:26:36,938
Hermann,
uncuff them.

1791
02:26:55,582 --> 02:26:59,586
I'm officially surrendering myself over
to you, Lieutenant Raine.

1792
02:27:00,712 --> 02:27:02,505
We're your prisoners.

1793
02:27:03,339 --> 02:27:05,049
How about my knife?

1794
02:27:11,014 --> 02:27:12,974
Thank you very much,
Colonel.

1795
02:27:13,057 --> 02:27:16,144
Utivich, cuff the Colonel's hands
behind his back.

1796
02:27:16,227 --> 02:27:18,438
Is that really
necessary?

1797
02:27:18,521 --> 02:27:20,607
I'm a slave
to appearances.

1798
02:27:23,776 --> 02:27:25,278
Scalp Hermann.

1799
02:27:26,946 --> 02:27:28,615
Are you mad?

1800
02:27:28,990 --> 02:27:30,742
What have you done?

1801
02:27:31,242 --> 02:27:34,579
I made a deal with your general
for that man's life!

1802
02:27:35,663 --> 02:27:39,042
Yeah, they made that deal. But they don't
give a fuck about him. They need you.

1803
02:27:39,125 --> 02:27:41,085
You'll be shot for this!

1804
02:27:41,753 --> 02:27:45,256
Nah, I don't think so. More like chewed out.
I've been chewed out before.

1805
02:27:46,591 --> 02:27:50,762
You know, Utivich and myself heard that
deal you made with the brass.

1806
02:27:51,220 --> 02:27:52,972
End the war tonight?

1807
02:27:54,390 --> 02:27:55,934
I'd make that deal.

1808
02:27:56,017 --> 02:27:57,852
How about you, Utivich?
You make that deal?

1809
02:27:57,936 --> 02:27:58,937
I'd make that deal.

1810
02:27:59,020 --> 02:28:01,522
I don't blame you.
Damn good deal.

1811
02:28:02,273 --> 02:28:05,401
And that pretty little nest
you feathered for yourself.

1812
02:28:05,485 --> 02:28:08,863
Well, if you're willing to barbecue
the whole High Command,

1813
02:28:08,947 --> 02:28:11,950
I suppose that's worth
certain considerations.

1814
02:28:12,700 --> 02:28:14,786
But I do have
one question.

1815
02:28:15,870 --> 02:28:18,623
When you get to your little place
on Nantucket Island,

1816
02:28:18,706 --> 02:28:23,253
I imagine you are going to take off that
handsome-looking SS uniform of yours.

1817
02:28:23,336 --> 02:28:24,671
Ain't you?

1818
02:28:28,633 --> 02:28:30,510
That's what I thought.

1819
02:28:31,261 --> 02:28:33,137
Now, that I can't abide.

1820
02:28:34,555 --> 02:28:36,849
How about you, Utivich,
can you abide it?

1821
02:28:36,933 --> 02:28:38,810
Not one damn bit, sir.

1822
02:28:40,436 --> 02:28:42,522
I mean,
if I had my way,

1823
02:28:43,022 --> 02:28:47,485
you'd wear that goddamn uniform for the rest
of your pecker-sucking life.

1824
02:28:48,987 --> 02:28:49,988
But I'm aware
that ain't practical.

1825
02:28:50,071 --> 02:28:53,116
I mean, at some point, you're
going to have to take it off.

1826
02:28:53,199 --> 02:28:54,325
So,

1827
02:28:55,285 --> 02:28:58,997
I'm going to give you a little
something you can't take off.

1828
02:29:23,938 --> 02:29:26,065
You know something,
Utivich?

1829
02:29:26,441 --> 02:29:29,235
I think this just might be
my masterpiece.

